commText: Mayank and Head are at the crease. Mayank is on strike. Kwena Maphaka will open the attack
Kwena Maphaka to Mayank, wide, gets some swing on this full toss, but it's down the leg-side. Kwena Maphaka starts off with a wide ball

Players with 200-plus IPL appearances for a team 239 - Virat Kohli (RCB) 222 - MS Dhoni (CSK) 200 - Rohit Sharma (MI)
Hardik Pandya to Mayank, 1 run, width on offer and Mayank cuts it to deep backward point for a single
Hardik Pandya to Head, 1 run, good fielding at cover. Was punched off the back foot by Head and the fielder stationed on the off-side stops it with a dive
Hardik Pandya to Mayank, no run, back of a length on middle and leg, nudged to mid-wicket by Mayank

Kwena Maphaka to Head, leg byes, 1 run, slower back of a length delivery on leg, cramps the batter for room. Head looks to heave it away, gets hit on the thigh pad as they scamper across for a leg bye
Kwena Maphaka to Mayank, 1 run, short and wide outside off, Mayank cuts it through backward point for a single
Kwena Maphaka to Head, SIX, right into the slot, a length delivery and Head heaves it over wide long-on for half-a-dozen. 78 metre maximum
Kwena Maphaka to Head, SIX, short of a length on middle and leg, Head picks the length early and clubs it over deep mid-wicket for back-to-back sixes.. That was close to 100 metre
Kwena Maphaka to Head, FOUR, carnage! Kwena Maphaka goes full and Head has drilled it straight past the bowler for a rollicking boundary. Young Kwena Maphaka put under pressure
Kwena Maphaka to Head, FOUR, 22 runs from the over! Short in length around off, Head guides it over the fielder at short third man as SRH are 40/0 after 3 overs
STAT: This is SRH's 10th opening pair since IPL 2022, only KKR have used more in this period (15)
Much needed change as MI's ace bowler comes into the attack
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Bumrah to Head, no run, slower delivery outside off, an off-cutter, Head swings and misses
Bumrah to Head, 1 run, yorker length delivery on middle and leg, Head digs it towards mid-wicket for a single
Bumrah to Mayank, 2 runs, short of a length on off, Mayank steers it to square third man for a couple of runs

Bumrah to Mayank, 1 run, yorker length delivery at the legs, Mayank flicks it to wide mid-on and takes a comfortable single

Hardik Pandya to Mayank, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Hardik Pandya to Mayank, out Caught by Tim David!! Hardik Pandya draws first blood! Goes short and quick on off, Mayank goes for a pull, but plays a half-hearted shot. Gets a top edge towards mid-on and Tim David doesn't miss out on the opportunity this time around. Mayank's short stay at the crease comes to an end.. Mayank c Tim David b Hardik Pandya 11(13) [4s-1]
Abhishek Sharma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Hardik Pandya to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, cramps the batter for room, a length ball that Abhishek Sharma knocks towards mid-off and takes a quick run
Hardik Pandya to Head, no run, short of a length around off, Head punches it firmly to mid-off
Hardik Pandya to Head, FOUR, quality shot! Hardik Pandya bangs it short and Head adjusts well to play it late, guiding it over short third man for four runs

Hardik Pandya to Head, FOUR, in the air, but safe! Was a full toss outside off and Head slices it uppishly towards point. The fielder stationed there dives to his right, but fails to get his hand to it
Mayank Agarwal vs Hardik Pandya in the IPL Runs: 7 Balls: 11 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 2.33 SR: 63.63
Hardik Pandya to Head, FOUR, hat-trick of boundaries to end the over. Head makes room and punches this firmly through cover for four more.. 13 runs from the over
Gerald Coetzee, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Gerald Coetzee to Abhishek Sharma, no ball, Gerald Coetzee starts off with a high full toss and the umpire signals a no ball. Hardik has reviewed it. Replays confirm it was over the waist and the next ball will be a free hit
Gerald Coetzee to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, free hit goes the distance! A short delivery by Gerald Coetzee and Abhishek Sharma nails the pull over fine leg as the ball clears the boundary comfortably
Gerald Coetzee to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, short of a length on off, Abhishek Sharma steers it to point for one
Gerald Coetzee to Head, FOUR, Head continues to march along. This was pitched up by the pacer and Head heaves it over mid-wicket for four runs. Carnage!
Gerald Coetzee to Head, FOUR, Head brings up his fifty! Makes room and crunches it through wide mid-off to bring up the milestone. This is pure entertainment
Gerald Coetzee to Head, SIX, short and punished! Picks the length early and nails the pull over deep square leg, just clears Tilak Verma who was leaping at the fence
Gerald Coetzee to Head, 1 run, SRH - 81/1 (6 overs).. A full length delivery by Gerald Coetzee and Head heaves it through square leg for a single. Coetzee goes for 23 runs in the over!

Strategic timeout! Hyderabad off to a flying start as the home crowd is getting entertained to the core. Head has set the stage on fire in his first game of the tournament. Will MI manage to stop him or will he continue to punish them? We shall find out soon..

Highlights (1-6 overs) - Maphaka becomes third youngest overseas player to debut in IPL - Head opens his account with a four - David drops Head on 5 off Hardik - Head smashes Maphaka for 6, 6, 4, 4 in his second over - Hardik dismisses Mayank and breaks the opening stand - Head smashes Hardik for a hat-trick of fours - Head brings up his fifty off 18 balls
Piyush Chawla, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chawla to Head, 1 run, tad short on off, punched along the carpet to long-off for a single

Chawla to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, on the shorter side, Abhishek Sharma goes for the aerial route and swings it over the fielder at long-on as he clears him comfortably

Fastest IPL fifties vs MI (by balls taken) 14 - Pat Cummins (KKR) - Pune, 2022 18 - Rishabh Pant (DC) - Mumbai WS, 2018 18 - Travis Head (SRH) - Hyderabad, 2024 19 - Ajinkya Rahane (CSK) - Mumbai WS, 2023
Chawla to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, dances down the wicket to drive this to wide long-off for a single
Chawla to Head, 1 run, tad short outside off, Head punches it through the off-side for a single
Chawla to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, 50-run stand up! A short ball by Chawla and Abhishek Sharma pulls it over deep backward square leg for a 74 metre maximum

Chawla to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, 100 up for Sunrisers Hyderabad in 7 overs! This is insane. Chawla goes short and Abhishek Sharma pulls it over wide long-on for a six to end the over. Chawla goes for 21 runs in his first over
Gerald Coetzee to Head, wide, fires a wide outside off, out of the batter's reach
Gerald Coetzee to Head, 1 run, a low full toss outside off, Head gets an outside edge towards the keeper, a fumble allows a single
Gerald Coetzee to Abhishek Sharma, byes, FOUR, banged in short by Gerald Coetzee and it beats Kishan's leap as he was trying to grab it with one hand
Gerald Coetzee to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, short and wide outside off, Abhishek Sharma smashes it over cover for a scintillating boundary. Gerald Coetzee under tremendous pressure

Gerald Coetzee to Head, out Caught by Naman Dhir!! Gerald Coetzee gets the big fish! A short and wide ball outside off, Head goes for an upper cut, but can't get the timing right. Was slightly slow as the fielder in the deep completes the formalities. Head walks back to the pavilion after playing a fantastic knock. Some respite for Gerald Coetzee! Head c Naman Dhir b Gerald Coetzee 62(24) [4s-9 6s-3]

Kwena Maphaka to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, yorker length ball on middle and leg, Abhishek Sharma gets an inside edge towards short fine leg where Bumrah fails to stop the ball, that races away at the rate of knots

Kwena Maphaka to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, no stopping Abhishek Sharma! A short ball by Kwena Maphaka and Abhishek Sharma has pulled it over deep square leg for a 84 metre six. Slower one that was sent into oblivion

Shams Mulani to Klaasen, 2 runs, SRH finish with 277. Fuller, quicker and outside off, Klaasen toe-ends the loft back over Mulani and Markram races back for the second. 21 off the final over..

21:20 Local Time, 15:50 GMT, 21:20 IST: Phew! Let's all take a breather. We have witnessed something special and need some time to get back to normalcy, at least I do. Where do we start? So much happened over the course of 20 overs. Let's start with the drop catch.. Tim David put down Travis Head on 5 in the second over of the innings and thus started the carnage. The Australian southpaw playing his first game of the season took apart young Kwena Maphaka to get his innings going. He reached his fifty off 18 balls and at that time it was the fastest for SRH in the history of IPL, only for Abhishek Sharma to break it a few overs later. The two left-handers were merciless; they were not prepared to take a back step and kept going for more even though they were getting over 10 runs per over. They stitched a 68-run stand in just 3.4 overs.

Klaasen: We got the best groundsmen in the world. Was an unbelievable wicket. They (top order batters) set the tempo at the front. There was a lot of pressure coming into this game. We have incredible batters up at the top.

Hardik broke the partnership and all thought that Mumbai Indians would stage a comeback, but we were wrong. Markram played the perfect second fiddle to his more powerful mates and added quick runs first with Abhishek and then with Klaasen. Mumbai even held back Bumrah for Klaasen; that match-up didn't work as the platform was set and the South African didn't have to take any risk against the ace pacer. He targeted the other bowlers and notched up his second fifty of the season. RCB held the highest IPL total for over 10 years and that was in jeopardy with the power-hitting, Klaasen managed to breach that in the final over of the innings and SRH now hold that record. Some of the Mumbai players like Bumrah and Hardik applauded their players as they walked back to the dugout. There were plenty of droopy shoulders and they need an uplifting if they are to compete in this game. Let's see how they respond to this mountain in front of them.. Back soon
